The WAV files where split into 30+ files in WinRAR so i could transport them to a computer with internet on my only working floppy disc. I miss those days of complete and utter chaos, where i just did whatever i wanted without worrying about the outcome.

The final three tracks on Fragments were improvisations on a broken toy piano where i only played the black keys, recorded on an ancient 486 through the built-in mic in the monitor and later slowed down and sped up multiple times, creating a bitcrushing effect.
Today is the 18th anniversary of my first EP, Silence In Space. Most of the tracks eventually ended up on Fragments, which was released later that same year. https://t.co/gacewNEEB5

@trashgh0st I bought a cheap MD Walkman and transfered some of my favorite music to old refurbished blanks so I don't get sad if they break. It's so nice being able to get away from social media and not having to deal with the music turning off when receiving a text.
@a_decimal I received anonymous death threats for saying no when someone on FB asked me publicly if I was going to have it cut off.
Today is supposed to be a day of joy but personally I feel like it should also be a day where we stand up and say ENOUGH IS ENOUGH!!!

We were promised change. We were promised to get a fair treatment in the healthcare system, but only the bare minimum was done and only because organizations such as Amnesty International were breathing down their necks.

People used to get furious at me when I said that I wished I lived in the US so I could get approved for trans healthcare but now it's getting worse and worse for each day and with Arkansas banning trans healthcare for minors, it seems like there's nowhere to run anymore.
A country where years of gatekeeping drives us to despair or worse, and where it's practically impossible to get approved if you're disabled or has a history of drug use.
I live in a country where it's easier to score blow than it is to get blockers. Where even though we have socialized healthcare, it's easier to become an airforce pilot than to get approved for hrt.
I have a lot of things on my mind that I feel needs to be said, but I'm struggling with finding the words right now.
Happy #TransDayOfVisibility everyone!!!
